title: Shoulder Exercises Post-Op
content: Peter Attia films his week 9 post-op PT session with Kyler Brown where they walk through 11 shoulder exercises. These exercises are great even if youâ€™re not recovering from surgery.

title: Isometric Shoulder Exercises
content: This video includes several isometric shoulder exercises, including shoulder extension, shoulder flexion, and shoulder external rotation. These exercises can help improve shoulder strength and stability.

title: Assisted Flexion/Supination with Core Activation and Diaphragmatic Breathing
content: This exercise involves assisted flexion and supination with core activation and diaphragmatic breathing. It can help improve shoulder mobility and stability.

title: Ipsilateral Rotation With Banded Hip and Shoulder Facilitation
content: This exercise involves ipsilateral rotation with banded hip and shoulder facilitation. It can help improve shoulder and hip mobility and stability.

title: Bilateral Banded External Rotation
content: This exercise involves bilateral banded external rotation with three hand positions. It can help improve shoulder strength and stability.

title: Kickstand RDL with External Rotation Isometric the Shoulder
content: This exercise involves a kickstand RDL with external rotation isometric the shoulder. It can help improve shoulder and hip mobility and stability.

title: Reverse Lunge with Isometric Row
content: This exercise involves a reverse lunge with isometric row. It can help improve shoulder and back strength and stability.

title: Isometric Cuff walk-outs
content: This exercise involves isometric cuff walk-outs, which can help increase load tolerance without motion to the joint.

title: Rotator Cuff Eccentrics
content: This video includes rotator cuff eccentrics, which can help improve shoulder strength and stability.

title: Rotator Cuff Eccentric with Drop sets
content: This exercise involves rotator cuff eccentric with drop sets, which can help improve shoulder strength and stability.
